$ System.Net.Security.SslStream (class)
@ System.Net.Security.SslStream

`System.Net.Security.SslStream` derives from `System.Net.Security.AuthenticatedStream` and
provides a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/Stream[Stream] for → development/security/cryptography/SSL-TLS communication.

{ Simple HTTPS Client #SslStream-HTTPS-Client

  The following simple example demonstrate how `System.Net.Security.SslStream` can be combined with `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Net/Sockets/TcpClient` to establish
  establish → development/web/HTTPS connection:
code {
$domain = 'renenyffenegger.ch'
$conn  = new-object System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient($domain, 443)

[System.Net.Sockets.NetworkStream] $connStream = $conn.GetStream()

$sslStream = New-Object System.Net.Security.SslStream($connStream,$false)
$sslStream.AuthenticateAsClient($domain)

$reader = new-object System.IO.StreamReader($sslStream)
$writer = new-object System.IO.StreamWriter($sslStream)

$writer.AutoFlush = $true

#
#    Send → development/web/HTTP/request[request] header, terminated
#    by an empty line
#
$writer.WriteLine('GET / HTTP/1.1')
$writer.WriteLine("Host: $domain")
$writer.WriteLine('')

#
#    Read response from server.
#
while ($reader.Peek() -ne -1) {
   write-host ($reader.ReadLine())
}
code }

}

